20associations%2C%20failed%20to%20reach%20an%20agreement%20on%20a%20new%20contract.%20Workers'%20demands%20included%20higher%20wages%20and%20promises%20of%20job%20security%20amid%20increasing%20automation%20in%20the%20shipping%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20labor%20stoppage%20could%20end%20up%20costing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsumer-products-most-likely-to-be-impacted-by-port-strike-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomy%20billions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdockworker-strike-what-will-be-impacted-prices-inflation-martime-longshoremen-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esnarl%20supply%20chains%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20process.%20But%20the%20strike%20is%20more%20than%20just%20a%20test%20of%20the%20economy%3B%20it's%20also%20a%20test%20of%20Biden%2C%20who%2C%20if%20he%20chose%20to%20do%20so%2C%20could%20step%20in%20and%20use%20the%20power%20of%20government%20to%20break%20the%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nlrb.gov%2Fabout-nlrb%2Fwho-we-are%2Four-history%2F1947-taft-hartley-passage-and-nlrb-structural-changes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETaft-Hartley%20Act%20of%201947%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20controversial%20aspect%20of%20US%20labor%20law.%20Under%20that%20legislation%2C%20presidents%20are%20given%20the%20power%20to%20intervene%20and%20seek%20a%20court%20injunction%20to%20force%20unions%20to%20return%20to%20work%20and%20reopen%20negotiations%20in%20situations%20when%20they%20deem%20national%20health%20and%20security%20at%20risk.%20In%202002%2C%20then-President%20George%20W.%20Bush%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2002%2F10%2F09%2Fus%2Fpresident-invokes-taft-hartley-act-to-open-29-ports.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estepped%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20do%20just%20that%20during%20a%20West%20Coast%20port%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20don't%20expect%20Biden%20to%20do%20the%20same.%20Despite%20calls%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnrf.com%2Fmedia-center%2Fpress-releases%2Fnrf-calls-administration-use-any-and-all-authority-end-port-strike%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretailers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnam.org%2Fmanufacturers-call-on-president-to-invoke-taft-hartley-act-to-stop-port-strike-32188%2F%3Fstream%3Dpolicy-legal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanufacturers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20invoke%20the%20act%2C%20Biden%20said%20on%20September%2030%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehe%20won't%20intervene%2C%20giving%20the%20rationale%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20collective%20bargaining%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20believe%20in%20Taft-Hartley.%26quot%3B%20It's%20a%20position%20consistent%20with%20his%20longtime%20efforts%20to%20support%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECathy%20Creighton%2C%20the%20director%20of%20Cornell%20University's%20Industrial%20and%20Labor%20Relations%20Buffalo%20Co-Lab%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20while%20Biden%20is%20saying%20he%20won't%20step%20in%20right%20now%2C%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20he%20won't%20if%20the%20strike%20continues.%20Even%20so%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20is%20likely%20not%20inclined%20to%20supersede%20what%20workers%20want%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20employee's%20decision%20to%20strike%2C%26quot%3B%20Creighton%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20vote.%20So%20that%20would%20mean%20overcoming%20the%20vote%20of%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20workers%20who%20wanted%20to%20strike.%20And%20so%20it's%20probably%20not%20this%20administration's%20inclination%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20history%20shows%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20if%20he%20later%20decided%20to%20intervene%20in%20the%20strike%2C%20it%20could%20infuriate%20workers.%20As%20Creighton%20noted%2C%20Biden%20received%20blowback%20from%20the%20labor%20movement%20after%20asking%20Congress%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenate-votes-stop-rail-strike-no-paid-sick-days-workers-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintervene%20in%20a%20potential%20rail%20strike%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20December%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20right%20to%20strike%20is%20fundamental%20and%20no%20president%20can%20claim%20to%20be%20pro-union%20unless%20he%20respects%20that%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamilton%20Nolan%2C%20a%20labor%20journalist%20and%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Hammer%3A%20Power%2C%20Inequality%2C%20and%20the%20Struggle%20for%20the%20Soul%20of%20Labor%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20not%20intervening%20he%20will%20demonstrate%20that%20even%20large%20strikes%20in%20logistically%20important%20industries%20can%20play%20out%20like%20any%20other%20strike%2C%20and%20be%20settled%20to%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20workers%2C%20and%20life%20will%20carry%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Nolan%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20government%20always%20cuts%20off%20the%20ability%20of%20unions%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20most%20impactful%20strike%2C%20that%20is%20a%20terrible%20and%20detrimental%20act%20of%20limiting%20how%20strong%20workers%20in%20this%20country%20can%20ever%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ILA%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20BI's%20request%20for%20comment.%20In%20a%20statement%2C%20USMX%20said%20that%20they%20have%20%26quot%3Bdemonstrated%20a%20commitment%20to%20doing%20our%20part%20to%20end%20the%20completely%20avoidable%20ILA%20strike.%20Our%20current%20offer%20of%20a%20nearly%2050%25%20wage%20increase%20exceeds%20every%20other%20recent%20union%20settlement%2C%20while%20addressing%20inflation%2C%20and%20recognizing%20the%20ILA's%20hard%20work%20to%20keep%20the%20global%20economy%20running.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2024%2F10%2F01%2Fstatement-from-president-joe-biden-on-the-negotiations-between-usmx-and-the-international-longshoremens-association%2F%5C%22%20tar